>>>>> # Looking for support? Here's how we can help
>>>>> Whether you are looking to join one of our local groups and have a chat
over a cup of tea, pick up literature with the latest information or phone our
helpline, there are many ways in which we can support you with your diabetes.
>>>>> We support people across the South West who are affected by diabetes,
whether you or someone you know has been recently diagnosed, or if you have
been living with Type 1 or Type 2 diabetes for a long time, or if you are a
>>>>> Here are some of the ways that we can help:
>>>>> We have different types of groups across our region run by our
>>>>> Our adult groups help support people with Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes.
Many groups run meetings where you can find out the latest information in a
social and friendly environment. Some groups also have a Facebook page where
you join an online community to chat and share experiences with others.
>>>>> Go to our Listing of Local Groups page to find your nearest one.
>>>>> You can also volunteer with our local groups and get involved with a
range of activities from fundraising to organising events.
>>>>> Being diagnosed and living with diabetes at an early age can feel
daunting and confusing. Our children and families groups provide face to face
support, organising events where parents and children meet up, have fun and
>>>>> Go to our Listing of Local Groups page to find your nearest one.
>>>>> You can also volunteer with our local children's and families' groups.
For more information, please phone or email our South West team at
>>>>> As well as lots of great information on our guide to diabetes we have a
range of printed materials about living with diabetes that you may find
useful. If you want us to send these out to you then please email or phone the
>>>>> You can contact our helpline service on 0345 123 2399 for advice and
support. We have advisors with counselling skills and an extensive knowledge
of diabetes. It’s the cost of a local call and the service is available
between 9am and 7pm on Monday to Friday.
>>>>> If you are struggling to resolve a specific issue relating to your
diabetes then we may be able to help. For advice please phone or email the
>>>>> Email the South West office at south.west@diabetes.org.uk
>>>>> Someone is diagnosed with diabetes every two minutes. Your donation can
